data.name: ReportTemplate_Query_Group_Description
data.value:
Up to 5 query selection options can be selected for report. There are three colum settings:
* __Query Selection__: selects the data source used to filter the report output. * __Mandatory__: set the query option to mandatory to generate a report. * __Operator__: defines how the seletion value will be treated the default is 'Equal to'

data.name: ReportTemplate_Column_Structure_Description
data.value:
Report template structure, enables you to order and structure the report once you have selected your fields.
- __Column Source__: defines the data source for the column. - __Order__: defines the order of the columns across the report. - __Grouping Header__: will group the report based on the column value. - __Grouping Type__: will select the type of grouping. - __Selection Level__: will select the section a column will be displayed.
__Note__, a section level must be selected for each grouping header. Non grouping header fields will be deisplayed in the same section level as the grouping header.

data.name: Form_Field_Selection_Options_Field_Description
data.value:
All selection options consist if a value and a description separated by ';'.
A simple selection option consist if a text string where the options are separeated by ';'. Both the option value and description have the same text string. E.g. Option1;Option 2;Option 3.
Complex selections option consists of string of text where the options are separated by ';' and each option value and description is separated by a ':'. E.g. O1:Option1;O2:Option 2;O3:Option3.
__Note__: all of the options must be either a simple or complex options and spaces can be inserted between ';' and ':' and new lines can be used to separate the options.
